content.text:
Let me analyze the images and provide a detailed solution:

Main Target Image Analysis:
- The structure consists of 7 blocks: 1 blue block in the center, 6 orange blocks surrounding and on top
- Structure has 2 layers
- Blue block forms the core/base
- Orange blocks are positioned symmetrically around the blue center block
- Top layer has a single orange vertical block

Block Dictionary Selection:
- Blue Block (Center): Index 1 (small blue cube)
- Orange Blocks:
  - Side blocks: Index 5 (horizontal orange cylinder)
  - Angled top blocks: Index 11 (angled orange block)
  - Vertical top block: Index 4 (vertical orange cylinder)

Assembly Instructions:
{
    Step1: Move block with index 1 (blue center block)
    Step2: Move block with index 5 (orange horizontal cylinder) to left side
    Step3: Move block with index 5 (orange horizontal cylinder) to right side
    Step4: Move block with index 5 (orange horizontal cylinder) to front
    Step5: Move block with index 5 (orange horizontal cylinder) to back
    Step6: Move block with index 11 (angled orange block) to front-left
    Step7: Move block with index 11 (angled orange block) to front-right
    Step8: Move block with index 11 (angled orange block) to back-left
    Step9: Move block with index 11 (angled orange block) to back-right
    Step10: Move block with index 4 (vertical orange cylinder) to top center
}
